    <briefdescription>
<para>Condition verifying the pool has enough inactive entities. </para>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para><ref refid="classhelios_1_1engine_1_1runtime_1_1spawn_1_1policy_1_1conditions_1_1RequestedAmountIsAvailableCondition" kindref="compound">RequestedAmountIsAvailableCondition</ref> checks whether the entity pool contains at least as many inactive (recyclable) entities as the spawn request requires. This prevents spawn failures due to pool exhaustion.</para>
<para>## Behavior</para>
<para><itemizedlist>
<listitem><para>Returns `true` if `requestedAmount &lt;= poolSnapshot.inactiveCount`</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>Resets the spawn timer on commit (via `setSinceLastSpawn(0)`)</para>
</listitem></itemizedlist>
</para>
<para>## Usage</para>
<para>```cpp auto condition = std::make_unique&lt;RequestedAmountIsAvailableCondition&gt;();</para>
<para>// Often combined with other conditions auto combined = std::make_unique&lt;SpawnConditionAll&gt;( std::make_unique&lt;TimerCondition&gt;(2.0f), std::make_unique&lt;RequestedAmountIsAvailableCondition&gt;() ); ```</para>
<para><simplesect kind="see"><para><ref refid="classhelios_1_1engine_1_1runtime_1_1spawn_1_1policy_1_1SpawnCondition" kindref="compound">SpawnCondition</ref> </para>
</simplesect>
<simplesect kind="see"><para><ref refid="classhelios_1_1engine_1_1runtime_1_1spawn_1_1policy_1_1SpawnConditionAll" kindref="compound">SpawnConditionAll</ref> </para>
</simplesect>
<simplesect kind="see"><para>GameObjectPoolSnapshot </para>
</simplesect>
</para>
